blog.description:
Hello! I go by Txen (or Wodka, I suppose), and I'm a 27 year old game developer living in Chicago. This blog will contain a lot of Transformers, Venom, Danganronpa, Ancient Magus Bride, TAZ, and whatever else suits my attention span.

Art Tag - Cosplay Tag

summary:
Still staggering from the 10/3 Chicago show... I was #775 in GA and 
we managed to snag a great spot near the extended stage. I...
caption:
Still staggering from the 10/3 Chicago show… I was #775 in GA and we managed to snag a great spot near the extended stage. I heard about a few faintings/rude people elsewhere but in our section everyone was luckily very courteous! This was my first ever concert period hahaha so you know… go big or go home

Most of the really big dance numbers were in the back and harder to see, but to be honest as much as I love those dances I’m not sure I’d trade the intimate interactions up front for anything ;o; We got baptized by water bottle spray at least 3 times and Jungkook basically did it with a full-ass bottle lmao so half of my face got soaked

A few highlights!

  • At the very end of Serendipity, Jimin got shy because people were cheering so much so he started giggling and couldnt finish the last line… adorable.
  • I love Seesaw but went in completely blind about what Yoongi’s choreo would be… HE’S BROUGHT IN DRAPED OVER A COUCH and collapses back down at the end of the song lmao like how on-brand… just let this goth boy sleep
  • J-Hope has been getting SO MUCH BETTER at English (they all are) and I’m very proud of him but also very glad they got a translator for the ending talks so that Yoongi and Jungkook could express themselves more freely in Korean
  • SO MANY ABS UHHH idk what it is about the Chicago shows but they were just tugging up each others shirts at every opportunity lmfao
  • Tae was precious and hamming it up constantly, honestly Jimin was very outgoing and happy the whole night too, smiling a ton and climbing over the lights to get closer to us. everyone was really just bringing their best, i didn’t notice even a single pitchy note

I feel sorta silly about it but I started crying as they sang the finale and wished us all goodbye… it was just very emotionally charged, and they truly try to circle the stage and make eye contact with every single person in the pit to make that connection and make fans feel appreciated and seen, they know how important they are to some people and seem to sincerely try not to take that for granted

I still kinda tear up at the drop of a hat thinking about it lmfao ugh what’s wrong with me x’D
